columns.name: name
columns.description: The name of the Web ACL. You cannot change the name of a Web ACL after you create it.

columns.name: arn
columns.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the entity.

columns.name: associated_resources
columns.description: The array of Amazon Resource Names (ARNs) of the associated resources.

columns.name: id
columns.description: The unique identifier for the Web ACL.

columns.name: scope
columns.description: Specifies the scope of the Web ACL. Possibles values are: 'REGIONAL' and 'CLOUDFRONT'.

columns.name: description
columns.description: A description of the Web ACL that helps with identification.

columns.name: capacity
columns.description: The Web ACL capacity units(WCUs) currently being used by this resource.

columns.name: lock_token
columns.description: A token used for optimistic locking.

columns.name: managed_by_firewall_manager
columns.description: Indicates whether this web ACL is managed by AWS Firewall Manager.

columns.name: default_action
columns.description: The action to perform if none of the Rules contained in the Web ACL match.

columns.name: logging_configuration
columns.description: The logging configuration for the specified web ACL.

columns.name: pre_process_firewall_manager_rule_groups
columns.description: The first set of rules for AWS WAF to process in the web ACL.

columns.name: post_process_firewall_manager_rule_groups
columns.description: The last set of rules for AWS WAF to process in the web ACL.

columns.name: rules
columns.description: The Rule statements used to identify the web requests that you want to allow, block, or count.

columns.name: visibility_config
columns.description: Defines and enables Amazon CloudWatch metrics and web request sample collection.

columns.name: tags_src
columns.description: A list of tags associated with the resource.

columns.name: region
columns.description: The AWS Region in which the resource is located.
